      "source": [
        "# **Algoritmos de recomendación sobre una red social sintética**\n",
        "\n",
        "Notebook con los Algoritmos 1, 2 y 3 del TFM: topológico (PPR), semántico\n",
        "(NLP) e híbrido. El modelo híbrido se presenta primero en su versión de\n",
        "**tres dimensiones** (topología + semántica + personalidad) y después se\n",
        "**amplía a una cuarta dimensión** de intereses declarados. Ambos grids\n",
        "comparten exactamente el mismo grafo, los mismos embeddings y el mismo\n",
        "split, de modo que sus resultados son directamente comparables.\n",
        "Se cierra con la evaluación offline y la comparativa entre algoritmos.\n",
        "El Algoritmo 4 (red neuronal) se desarrolla en su propio notebook."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "id": "8bb2593d",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "8bb2593d"
      },
      "source": [
        "## **1. Setup, carga de datos y limpieza**\n",
        "\n",
        "Cargamos los cuatro CSV exportados por el simulador y fijamos la semilla.\n",
        "Renombramos `message_text;` a `message_text`."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "id": "57be4754",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "57be4754"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "!pip install -q sentence-transformers"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "id": "7688bdd4",
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "id": "7688bdd4",
        "outputId": "1f5495f9-8e25-4d09-87d4-25096ac7e56d"
      },
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
          "name": "stdout",
          "text": [
            "Usuarios: 220\n",
            "Amistades: 1450\n",
            "Interacciones: 2246\n",
            "Mensajes: 150\n"
          ]
        }
      ],
      "source": [
        "import math\n",
        "import random\n",
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "import pandas as pd\n",
        "import networkx as nx\n",
        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
        "\n",
        "from sentence_transformers import SentenceTransformer\n",
        "from sklearn.metrics.pairwise import cosine_similarity\n",
        "from tqdm import tqdm\n",
        "\n",
        "# Reproducibilidad\n",
        "SEED = 2908\n",
        "random.seed(SEED)\n",
        "np.random.seed(SEED)\n",
        "\n",
        "# messages e interactions son los archivos extendidos\n",
        "\n",
        "ids = {\n",
        "    'users':        '1Q00bSqmuaYMaPCC9T3ZWPSssOj8ULQAN',\n",
        "    'friendships':  '1cZY1aGP-ydnmy14IzU1FVsnx9AhocmN6',\n",
        "    'interactions': '1ZP2Q1n53lmpQ578nchEZbJn-_fbLhvVS',\n",
        "    'messages':     '1SYLiH-ySCqRDLTxpuzXgrrxKFoDXupe9',\n",
        "}\n",
        "\n",
        "def url(file_id):\n",
        "    return f'https://drive.google.com/uc?export=download&id={file_id}'\n",
        "\n",
        "import os\n",
        "def _load_csv(nombre_local, file_id):\n",
        "    # Carga local si el CSV está presente (ejecución offline); si no, desde Drive.\n",
        "    src = nombre_local if os.path.exists(nombre_local) else url(file_id)\n",
        "    return pd.read_csv(src, sep=',', quotechar='\"', on_bad_lines='warn')\n",
        "\n",
        "df_users        = _load_csv('users.csv',        ids['users'])\n",
        "df_friendships  = _load_csv('friendships.csv',  ids['friendships'])\n",
        "df_interactions = _load_csv('interactions.csv', ids['interactions'])\n",
        "df_messages     = _load_csv('messages.csv',     ids['messages'])\n",
        "\n",
        "# Renombrado de columna mal parseada\n",
        "if 'message_text;' in df_interactions.columns:\n",
        "    df_interactions = df_interactions.rename(columns={'message_text;': 'message_text'})\n",
        "\n",
        "# Normalización de textos (minúsculas, espacios, puntuación residual)\n",
        "df_messages['content']          = df_messages['content'].astype(str).str.strip().str.lower().str.rstrip(';')\n",
        "df_interactions['message_text'] = df_interactions['message_text'].astype(str).str.strip().str.lower().str.rstrip(';')\n",
        "\n",
        "print(f\"Usuarios: {len(df_users)}\")\n",
        "print(f\"Amistades: {len(df_friendships)}\")\n",
        "print(f\"Interacciones: {len(df_interactions)}\")\n",
        "print(f\"Mensajes: {len(df_messages)}\")"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "id": "44f50ad5",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "44f50ad5"
      },
      "source": [
        "## **2. Infraestructura común entre los algoritmos**"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "id": "32b5cac7",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "32b5cac7"
      },
      "source": [
        "Definimos tres construcciones que reutilizan los tres algoritmos: el grafo ponderado de relaciones,\n",
        "el diccionario de personalidad por usuario y el mapa de embeddings semánticos."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "id": "4f665251",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "4f665251"
      },
      "source": [
        "### ***2.1. Grafo ponderado de relaciones***"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "id": "40915162",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "40915162"
      },
      "source": [
        "Cada usuario es un nodo y el peso base de una amistad es 1.0. Sobre esa capa estática, sumamos una capa de interacciones con pesos crecientes según el coste cognitivo de la acción (`read=0.1`, `like=0.2`, `reply=0.4`, `share=0.6`). Si A interactúa con B pero no le sigue, creamos un enlace implícito con la mitad del peso.\n",
        "\n",
        "La función `build_weighted_graph` acepta cualquier subconjunto de interacciones, así nos sirve tanto para construir el grafo completo `G` (con todas las interacciones) como, más tarde, para construir el `G_train` (sólo con las interacciones del 80% de entrenamiento)."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "id": "65f5e41d",
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "id": "65f5e41d",
        "outputId": "bcf32622-f97d-4d11-8060-51fefd0dceab"
      },
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
          "name": "stdout",
          "text": [
            "G: 220 nodos, 2260 aristas\n"
          ]
        }
      ],
      "source": [
        "# Pesos por tipo de interacción según el coste cognitivo de la acción.\n",
        "# Las magnitudes concretas se validan en el análisis de sensibilidad (sección 4).\n",
        "interaction_weights = {'read': 0.1, 'like': 0.2, 'reply': 0.4, 'share': 0.6}\n",
        "\n",
        "def build_weighted_graph(df_users, df_friendships, df_interactions_subset, weights):\n",
        "    G = nx.DiGraph()\n",
        "    G.add_nodes_from(df_users['username'].dropna().unique())\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Capa estática de amistades\n",
        "    edges = [\n",
        "        (row['follower'], row['followed'], 1.0)\n",
        "        for _, row in df_friendships.iterrows()\n",
        "        if pd.notna(row['follower']) and pd.notna(row['followed'])\n",
        "    ]\n",
        "    G.add_weighted_edges_from(edges)\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Capa de interacciones (pesada y posiblemente implícita)\n",
        "    df = df_interactions_subset.copy()\n",
        "    df['w'] = df['interaction_type'].map(weights).fillna(0)\n",
        "    grouped = df.groupby(['username', 'message_author'])['w'].sum().reset_index()\n",
        "\n",
        "    for _, row in grouped.iterrows():\n",
        "        u, v, w = row['username'], row['message_author'], row['w']\n",
        "        if pd.isna(u) or pd.isna(v):\n",
        "            continue\n",
        "        if G.has_edge(u, v):\n",
        "            G[u][v]['weight'] += w\n",
        "        else:\n",
        "            G.add_edge(u, v, weight=w * 0.5)\n",
        "    return G\n",
        "\n",
        "# Grafo completo (sólo para los tests iniciales de los algoritmos)\n",
        "G = build_weighted_graph(df_users, df_friendships, df_interactions, interaction_weights)\n",
        "print(f\"G: {G.number_of_nodes()} nodos, {G.number_of_edges()} aristas\")"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "id": "a51fb262",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "a51fb262"
      },
      "source": [
        "### ***2.2. Vectorización de personalidad***\n",
        "\n",
        "Cada usuario tiene un vector en $\\{-1, 0, +1\\}^5$ con los cinco rasgos del modelo Big Five\n",
        "adaptado del simulador: Intellectual, Scrupulousness, Sociability, Friendliness, Neuroticism."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "id": "30c8fc0e",
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "id": "30c8fc0e",
        "outputId": "8358d836-1cee-420a-ba03-5286fd138c00"
      },
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
          "name": "stdout",
          "text": [
            "Intellectual       -> {np.float64(1.0): 145, np.float64(-1.0): 75}\n",
            "Scrupulousness     -> {np.float64(-1.0): 116, np.float64(1.0): 104}\n",
            "Sociability        -> {np.float64(1.0): 169, np.float64(-1.0): 51}\n",
            "Friendliness       -> {np.float64(-1.0): 113, np.float64(1.0): 107}\n",
            "Neuroticism        -> {np.float64(1.0): 152, np.float64(-1.0): 68}\n"
          ]
        }
      ],
      "source": [
        "RASGOS = ['Intellectual', 'Scrupulousness', 'Sociability', 'Friendliness', 'Neuroticism']\n",
        "\n",
        "def parse_traits_to_vector(trait_string):\n",
        "    if pd.isna(trait_string):\n",
        "        return np.zeros(5)\n",
        "    vector = np.zeros(5)\n",
        "    ts = str(trait_string)\n",
        "    for idx, nombre in enumerate(RASGOS):\n",
        "        if f'{nombre}+' in ts or f'{nombre} +' in ts:\n",
        "            vector[idx] = 1\n",
        "        elif f'{nombre}-' in ts or f'{nombre} -' in ts:\n",
        "            vector[idx] = -1\n",
        "    return vector\n",
        "\n",
        "df_users['traits_vector'] = df_users['traits'].apply(parse_traits_to_vector)\n",
        "personality_dict = dict(zip(df_users['username'], df_users['traits_vector']))\n",
        "\n",
        "# Diagnóstico rápido del sesgo de la red por rasgo\n",
        "import collections\n",
        "for i, name in enumerate(RASGOS):\n",
        "    valores = [v[i] for v in personality_dict.values()]\n",
        "    counts = collections.Counter(valores)\n",
        "    print(f\"{name:18s} -> {dict(counts)}\")"
      ]
    },
